What is APR?APR stands for Annual Percentage Rate. It's a measure used in the financial industry to compare the cost of loans or credit across different providers. The APR includes not only the interest rate but also any additional fees or costs associated with the loan, such as origination fees or other charges.

It is expressed as an annualized percentage and gives you a more comprehensive understanding of what it will actually cost you to borrow money over the course of a year. This makes it easier for consumers to compare different loans or credit products and make informed decisions about which one offers them the best deal.yes
